"title": "5355: invitations",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5355: invitations",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A request for attendance, often to a celebration or feast. Invitations to the blessings of the gospel are sometimes presented as requests to attend a banquet. In a negative sense one can be invited to sin.</p>\n<h2>Invitations to receive hospitality</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:15\">ACT 16:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:31-Gen24:33\">GEN 24:31–24:33</a> <em>Laban shows hospitality to Abraham's servant and his animals</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:54\">GEN 31:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:20\">EXO 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:29-Num10:32\">NUM 10:29–10:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:22-1Sam9:24\">1SA 9:22–9:24</a> <em>Saul dines with Samuel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:7\">1KI 13:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:4\">JOB 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:2\">JER 35:2</a>LUK <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:36\">7:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:37\">LUK 11:37</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:12\">JHN 21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:23\">ACT 10:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:27\">1CO 10:27</a></p>\n<h2>Invitations to a wedding or a banquet</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:8-Luke14:14\">LUK 14:8–14:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:4\">EST 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:12\">EST 5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:2\">JHN 2:2</a></p>\n<h2>Invitations requesting help</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:9\">ACT 16:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:3\">JDG 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:6\">JDG 11:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:7\">2KI 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:30-Acts8:31\">ACT 8:30–8:31</a></p>\n<h2>Invitations of the lovers in the Song of Solomon</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:13\">SNG 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:8\">SNG 4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:11\">SNG 7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song8:14\">SNG 8:14</a></p>\n<h2>Invitations to join in worshipping God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:3\">PSA 34:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:5-Ps66:6\">PSA 66:5–66:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:16\">PSA 66:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:1-Ps95:2\">PSA 95:1–95:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:5-Ps95:6\">PSA 95:5–95:6</a></p>\n<h2>Invitations of the Lord Jesus Christ to follow him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:19\">MAT 4:19</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:17\">MRK 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:10\">LUK 5:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21\">MAT 19:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:22\">LUK 18:22</a></p>\n<h2>Invitations to the blessings of the gospel</h2>\n<h3>Invitations given in varied terms</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:28-Matt11:30\">MAT 11:28–11:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:18\">ISA 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:10\">ZEC 3:10</a> <em>“to sit under his vine and fig-tree” refers to the peaceful security of the kingdom of God. See <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:25\">1Ki 4:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:4\">Mic 4:4</a></em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:34\">MAT 25:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:29\">JHN 4:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:20\">REV 3:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:17\">REV 22:17</a></p>\n<h3>Invitations using the imagery of a banquet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:16-Luke14:17\">LUK 14:16–14:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:1-Isa55:3\">ISA 55:1–55:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:1-Matt22:14\">MAT 22:1–22:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:7-Rev19:9\">REV 19:7–19:9</a></p>\n<h2>Invitations given with deceitful motives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:10-2Sam15:12\">2SA 15:10–15:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:23-2Sam13:29\">2SA 13:23–13:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:5-1Kgs1:10\">1KI 1:5–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh6:1-Neh6:8\">NEH 6:1–6:8</a></p>\n<h2>Invitations to do what is sinful</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:7\">GEN 39:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1-Gen3:4\">GEN 3:1–3:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:12\">GEN 39:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:15-Exod34:16\">EXO 34:15–34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:6\">NUM 22:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:11\">NUM 22:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:17\">NUM 22:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:7\">NUM 23:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:1-Num25:2\">NUM 25:1–25:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:10-Prov1:11\">PRO 1:10–1:11</a></p>",
